-- Lafontaine Open for Coalition in Saarland, Sueddeutsche Says
-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 2012-01-06T17:57:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/lafontaine-open-for-coalition-in-saarland-sueddeutsche-says.html
Germany ’s Left Party is open for
coalition talks with the Social Democrats and Greens after
German Chancellor Angela Merkel’s party ended its coalition with
the Free Democrats in the western state of Saarland today,
 Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported, citing an interview with Oskar Lafontaine, the party’s co-founder.  To contact the reporter on this story:
